### Next Steps
- [x] Create a `.specs/voice_chat_architecture.md` defining the WebSocket binary streaming format and backend routing logic.
- [x] Implement `AudioBroadcast` struct and a dedicated `audioUpdates` channel in `backend/internal/ws/hub.go`.
- [x] Add `AudioSend` channel to `Client` struct in `backend/internal/ws/client.go` to handle binary payloads.
- [x] Modify `ReadPump` and `WritePump` in `client.go` to handle `websocket.BinaryMessage` reading and writing.
- [x] Implement the audio broadcast routing logic in `hub.go` to route binary frames to clients on the same route.
- [x] Scaffold Go backend structures for audio rooms bound to presence routes, including admin permissions.
- [x] Define JSON message payloads for `voice:control` (mute, kick, disable).
- [x] Add `handleVoiceControl` method in `hub.go` to update `voiceRoutes` permissions safely.
- [x] Implement `voiceControl` handling in `ReadPump` for admin commands.
- [x] Create React atoms for voice state (`voicePermissionsAtom`, `globalVolumeAtom`).
- [x] Update `PresencePanel` to show a "Voice & Media" tab.
- [x] Build `VoicePanel` with Microphone toggle, Volume slider, and Admin toggles.
- [x] Intercept websocket binary frames for incoming audio packets (emitted as `voice:binary` event).
- [x] Setup Web Audio API `AudioContext` and packet queue to decode and play incoming Opus/WebM streams.
- [x] Embed media player for YouTube links syncing with global volume controls.
- [x] Enforce `home.manage` on backend `voice:control` messages using JWT permissions stored on the WebSocket client.
- [x] Raise the WebSocket read limit to support microphone chunk sizes beyond the previous 4 KiB JSON-era cap.
- [x] Add focused backend coverage for same-route audio fan-out, disabled/muted/kicked drops, and admin authorization.

